commit ccb79284006a42441b79450ff0769595c7390575
Author: Bernhard Rosenkränzer <bero@lindev.ch>
Date:   Tue Jun 16 05:05:49 2026 +0200

    Linux: replace glibmm/giomm + GTKWebKit with native Qt (QtWebEngine + QtDBus)
    
    - Full in-process QtWebEngine webview backend (removed WebKitGTK, compositor, separate helper process, all gi glue)
    - Ported dbus/xdp utilities, notifications (pure org.freedesktop.Notifications), MPRIS media controls, power save inhibit, screen reader, battery, last input, kglobalaccel registration, etc. to QtDBus
    - Removed generate_dbus, cppgir, glibmm subprojects and calls from active CMake paths
    - Autostart, URL scheme registration, file ops, launcher: direct .desktop + QSettings + QProcess/QDesktopServices (no xdg portals)
    - Set desktopFileName early; direct mimeapps.list manipulation for schemes (avoids xdg-mime/qtpaths fragility)
    - QtPositioning for geo location; other Qt fallbacks or DBus where the old gi paths were used
    - Remaining minimal stubs only for things without good portable Qt equivalent on Wayland without portals (global shortcuts now registers with kglobalaccel on Plasma Wayland/KWin; taskbar skip offered everywhere)
    - Verified clean build with ninja in preconfigured build/
    
    Eliminates the glibmm/GTKWebKit mismatch for this Qt app and for KDE Plasma/LXQt users.

